A vector is given. Print the biggest possible sum of a subset of that vector, considering that a subset may not contain consecutive elements of the vector.

Input:
vector

Output:
maximum possible sum of a subset with no consecutive elements from the original vector

Solution:
Using dynamic programming, optimized by using 2 states instead of the dp vector, there are the states:
prev0 for i - 2 and prev1 for i - 1. For prev0 we include the max sum up to that element, also adding the current element. For prev1, we include only the sum up to the previous element.

Complexity:

T: O(n) // we traverse the vector exactly once
S: O(1) // using 2 variables instead of an array reduces the space complexity from O(n).